      • createCustomModel

        @Nullable
public java.util.List<ValueObject> createCustomModel()
                                                         throws BizViolation
        This method can be overriden to create a custom in-memory model for ZTable. If this method is overriden, createQuery() won't be called. The default return value 'null' tells the framework to create the table model according to the variform definition.
        Returns:
        List
        Throws:
        BizViolation

      • getOrderings

        @Nullable
public Ordering[] getOrderings()
        This method can be overriden to change the default sorting order to the domain query. By default the first two columns are the sorted by.
        Returns:
        Ordering[]
